revision.text:
{{DISPLAYTITLE:Door_CloseWaitOpen}} {{Special|249|tag, speed, delay, lighttag|Door|CloseWaitOpen}} * ''tag'': Tag of affected sector * ''speed'': How quickly the door moves * ''delay'': Octics until door opens * ''lighttag'': Tag of sector to perform a gradual lighting effect in
Closes the specified door, and opens it again after delay octics have passed. If ''tag'' is 0, then the sector on the line's back side is used.
If lighttag is non-zero, a gradual lighting effect is done in the tagged sectors. The light is gradually changed between the darkest neighboring sector when the door is fully closed and the brightest neighboring sector when the door is fully open.
== Examples == {{noexamples}}
== Conversions from linedef types == The following Doom map format types can be converted as Door_CloseWaitOpen: {| {{prettytable}} !Type!!Conversion!!Trigger |- |{{icon|Doom}} 16:W1 Door Close + Open || Door_CloseWaitOpen (tag, {{xlat|D_SLOW}}, 240) || Player Cross |- |{{icon|Doom}} 76:WR Door Close + Open || Door_CloseWaitOpen (tag, {{xlat|D_SLOW}}, 240) || Player Cross, Repeatable |- |{{icon|Boom}} 175:S1 Door Close + Open || Door_CloseWaitOpen (tag, {{xlat|D_SLOW}}, 240) || Player Use |- |{{icon|Boom}} 196:SR Door Close + Open || Door_CloseWaitOpen (tag, {{xlat|D_SLOW}}, 240) || Player Use, Repeatable |}
